<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="glad-adj">glad <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɡlæd/    美 /ɡlæd/  </p>
<p>[无比较级]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于名词前] 高兴的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm <strong>glad about</strong> your passing the test.
你考试及格了,我很高兴。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) glad to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm glad to see you looking so well.
很高兴看到你气色这么好。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) glad + (that)/ wh- 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I'm glad we can be friends now.
很高兴我们现在成了朋友。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>感激的；庆幸的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was very <strong>glad of</strong> her warm coat in the biting wind.
她很庆幸在刺骨的寒风中有暖融融的大衣。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>I'd be glad if</strong> you can consider my recommendation.
如果您能考虑我的推荐我将非常感激。</p><footer>2014 浙江书面表达改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>gladly /'ɡlædli/ adv   </p></div>